1
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:39,500
<i>She is in a transient coma
right now.</i>

2
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:41,567
<i> Temporary type of coma.</i>

3
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:44,633
<i>I think it's better if we go
home and get some rest for now.</i>

4
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:45,700
<i> I will stay with Jessica.</i>

5
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:47,267
<i>I want to be here
when she wakes up.</i>

6
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:50,233
<i>- I'll stay here with you.
- Hazel caused trouble again.</i>

7
00:00:50,367 --> 00:00:51,333
<i>She ended up hurting
her daughter.</i>

8
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:54,300
<i>So she does hurt her own
daughter, too.</i>

9
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:56,533
<i>Perhaps what your dad said
is true,</i>

10
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:59,100
<i> that Hazel is hurting them.</i>

11
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:01,400
<i>Never in my wildest imagination
did I think</i>

12
00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:03,233
<i>I would stay in jail
for this long.</i>

13
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:05,100
<i>I didn't get any sleep worrying
about my daughter.</i>

14
00:01:05,233 --> 00:01:07,067
<i>Don't you dare get near
my daughter.</i>

15
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,467
<i>I'm not leaving this place
until I see my daughter.</i>

16
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:12,467
<i>I won't allow my child to see
the person who hurt her.</i>

17
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:14,100
<i> I need to go to Jessica.</i>

18
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:16,167
<i> I need to get close to her.</i>

19
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:17,667
<i> Sweetie...</i>

20
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:18,833
<i> Please forgive me, Jessica.</i>

21
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:20,567
<i>I didn't mean for this
to happen.</i>

22
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,067
<i> Sorry. I'm sorry.</i>

23
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,500
Sorry.

24
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:27,733
I admit, Sweetie.

25
00:01:29,767 --> 00:01:32,267
I was wrong to ruin your party.

26
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,067
But...

27
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:40,867
I couldn't control myself
because...

28
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:44,067
Because it hurts so much.

29
00:01:45,133 --> 00:01:48,600
What your dad did really hurts.

30
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:51,400
What both of you did
hurts so much.

31
00:01:55,067 --> 00:01:56,433
I just want you, Sweetie...

32
00:01:58,933 --> 00:02:00,333
to come back to me.

33
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:03,633
Let's forget all that happened.

34
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:06,133
Let's start over.

35
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:11,733
I just want our family back.

36
00:02:12,767 --> 00:02:13,733
That's all I want.

37
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:16,733
But...

38
00:02:18,733 --> 00:02:20,400
But you got hurt.

39
00:02:22,567 --> 00:02:23,967
Sweetie...

40
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:25,400
I didn't mean for this
to happen.

41
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:29,367
And I won't be able
to forgive myself...

42
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,233
if something bad were
to happen to you.

43
00:02:31,367 --> 00:02:32,633
My God.

44
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:38,300
So, Sweetie...

45
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:40,433
please wake up.

46
00:02:40,567 --> 00:02:42,167
Wake up, Sweetie.

47
00:02:43,233 --> 00:02:45,067
Mommy's here now.

48
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,567
I love you so much.

49
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:53,933
Jessica.

50
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,600
<i> Don't fight with her.</i>

51
00:02:55,733 --> 00:02:56,833
<i> Stop it!</i>

52
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,367
<i>- Jessica!
- Jessica!</i>

53
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:04,200
<i> Jessica!</i>

54
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,133
- Sweetie, you're awake!
- Mommy!

55
00:03:08,267 --> 00:03:09,900
Sweetie, you're awake!

56
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:12,533
- Sweetie, you're awake!
- Mommy, leave me alone!

57
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:17,067
Mommy, don't come any closer!

58
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:20,167
No! No!

59
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,133
<i> No! No!</i>

60
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,633
That's Jessica!

61
00:03:23,767 --> 00:03:24,633
Nurse!

62
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:26,633
Nurse, our patient is awake!

63
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:28,600
- Dad! Dad!
- No! No, I won't hurt you

64
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,067
Sweetie, don't be scared.

65
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,667
No! Don't come near me, please!

66
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,800
- Dad!
- Sweetie.

67
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:34,833
Don't be scared of me, sweetie.

68
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:36,333
I won't hurt you.

69
00:03:36,467 --> 00:03:37,733
Sweetie, don't be scared.

70
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,067
Auntie Felma!

71
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,333
How did you get in here?

72
00:03:41,467 --> 00:03:43,200
Manuel, our daughter's awake!

73
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:44,433
Jessica's awake.

74
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:47,100
- No! Dad!
- Sweetie, calm down.

75
00:03:47,233 --> 00:03:48,467
Leave me alone!

76
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,233
- Don't come near me!
- Please leave. Nurse!

77
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:53,500
I'm also a nurse,
I know what I'm doing.

78
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:54,800
She's my daughter!

79
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:57,767
Hazel, that's enough.

80
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:59,133
- Jessica!
- Come on!

81
00:03:59,267 --> 00:04:00,300
No, you can't!

82
00:04:03,133 --> 00:04:05,267
She's my daughter!
I know what to do! Wait!

83
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,833
Hazel, what are you doing here?

84
00:04:06,967 --> 00:04:07,900
What are you doing?

85
00:04:08,033 --> 00:04:09,233
- Hazel!
- Let go of me

86
00:04:09,367 --> 00:04:10,567
No! Hazel!

87
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,033
Didn't you hear your daughter?

88
00:04:12,167 --> 00:04:13,533
Don't you feel bad for her?

89
00:04:13,667 --> 00:04:14,867
She's afraid of you!

90
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,000
That's why I want to explain
that it was just an accident.

91
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:19,600
I didn't mean to hurt...

92
00:04:19,733 --> 00:04:21,033
- That's enough!
- Accident or not...

93
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:23,800
She was traumatized
because of what you did!

94
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:26,333
No, she's disoriented.

95
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:27,700
Didn't you see it?

96
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:29,100
She woke up.

97
00:04:29,233 --> 00:04:30,967
She woke up because of my voice.

98
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:33,467
She heard her mother's voice,
that's why...

99
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,233
Let me go back inside!

100
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:37,533
- Come on! stop that!
- Stay away from here!

101
00:04:37,667 --> 00:04:39,367
You want to be a mom, don't you!

102
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,167
Then act like one!

103
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:43,400
Think about her needs,
don't just do what you want!

104
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:46,300
Who are you to teach me
how to be a mom to my daughter?

105
00:04:46,433 --> 00:04:48,300
Who do you think you are?
Jessica!

106
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:49,533
Guard! Guard!

107
00:04:49,667 --> 00:04:50,733
Leave me be!

108
00:04:50,867 --> 00:04:53,033
- Take her away!
- Let me go to her! Wait!

109
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:55,333
- Let's go, let's go over there.
- Wait!

110
00:04:55,467 --> 00:04:57,133
My daughter! Manuel!

111
00:04:57,267 --> 00:04:59,500
Jessica is my daughter!

112
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,900
Jessica!

113
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,900
I'm glad you stopped her!

114
00:05:10,033 --> 00:05:11,300
I will take care
of everything here, Sis.

115
00:05:11,433 --> 00:05:12,400
Don't you worry.

116
00:05:12,533 --> 00:05:13,667
<i> By the way, Sis,</i>

117
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,000
<i>I have Abel here with me today.</i>

118
00:05:15,133 --> 00:05:16,700
<i>I asked him for help
for the deliveries.</i>

119
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:19,500
<i> The schedule is all messed up.</i>

120
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:20,767
Thank you, Darling.

121
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:21,633
Thank you.

122
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:25,067
If Jeffrey handles all that,

123
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,733
<i> we won't have a problem.</i>

124
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:28,733
Yes, I agree.

125
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:34,867
Sis, you're going home to get
some rest, don't you?

126
00:05:35,033 --> 00:05:36,500
Not yet, Sis.

127
00:05:36,633 --> 00:05:39,633
Manuel and Jessica
needed me here.

128
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,033
Paz!

129
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:46,633
What? I didn't say anything.

130
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:49,800
Yes, you didn't say anything,
but your face says it all.

131
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:51,633
Come on, Sis,

132
00:05:51,767 --> 00:05:55,867
it's like you're proving Hazel's
accusation

133
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,233
that you're acting like a mother
to her child.

134
00:05:59,367 --> 00:06:03,333
<i>Sis, of course, I can't just
leave Manuel here.</i>

135
00:06:03,467 --> 00:06:05,267
The man is practically disabled.

136
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:08,867
Oh, they're here.

137
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,200
- Okay, bye.
- Okay, bye, Sis.

138
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:28,500
Thank you.

139
00:06:46,567 --> 00:06:47,900
That damn woman.

140
00:06:48,733 --> 00:06:50,400
I was humiliated twice.

141
00:06:52,633 --> 00:06:53,900
I can't let this happen.

142
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:55,633
This can't happen.

143
00:06:59,733 --> 00:07:05,233
Madame Hazel, let's just focus
on the complaints

144
00:07:05,367 --> 00:07:07,767
that they filed
against you, okay?

145
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,067
Well, about
the restaurant's complaints,

146
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,300
it will be easy to handle.

147
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:15,233
You can just pay
for the damages,

148
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,633
and they won't go
after you anymore.

149
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,967
What about my husband?

150
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:29,367
About your husband,

151
00:07:30,667 --> 00:07:36,200
he filed a physical assault case
resulting in a serious injury.

152
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,867
That's up to 6 years in jail.

153
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:43,433
See?

154
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:45,867
Instead of antagonizing Manuel,

155
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,667
you should ask him
to drop the case.

156
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,200
Madam...

157
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,900
thank you so much.

158
00:08:00,033 --> 00:08:01,367
I have to get going.

159
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:06,933
I'll walk you out.

160
00:08:18,367 --> 00:08:19,567
How's the interview?

161
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:25,567
It didn't go well.

162
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,433
They said I'm qualified.

163
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:35,200
But I didn't have
a college degree,

164
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,333
so they rejected me.

165
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:41,633
There are many jobs out there
that don't require a diploma.

166
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:43,667
Construction worker,

167
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:46,200
restaurant crew,
parking attendant.

168
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,767
Daisy, I was a delivery
supervisor at FMP.

169
00:08:49,867 --> 00:08:51,700
I didn't have an issue
with the jobs you mentioned.

170
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:52,833
Those are good suggestions.

171
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:54,733
But it's not for me.

172
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,333
It will be hard for me, I'm not
used to doing those jobs.

173
00:08:56,467 --> 00:08:57,900
Be patient, Jeff.

174
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:02,300
You won't find a job
if you don't persevere.

175
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:04,067
Daisy, can you please stop
lecturing me?

176
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,033
Even my own mom doesn't
lecture me like that.

177
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:11,233
I'll find a job eventually.

178
00:09:11,367 --> 00:09:12,533
When?

179
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,333
You went through all
your savings, didn't you?

180
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:19,967
If you're looking
for an easy job,

181
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,667
then return to FMP.

182
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:31,767
What happened?

183
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:35,033
Mrs. Cruz versus Mrs Cruz
go at it again, didn't they?

184
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:37,867
No, you're wrong, Darling.

185
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,233
Miss Ruiz versus Mrs. Cruz.

186
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:46,633
Remember? That witch took
my best friend's title.

187
00:09:46,767 --> 00:09:50,100
Oh my gosh! Seriously,
that home wrecker...

188
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:51,267
Oh, my!

189
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,533
You'd better watch out, Abel,

190
00:09:52,667 --> 00:09:56,167
if I find out that
you have a mistress

191
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:59,300
I will shut down your future!

192
00:09:59,433 --> 00:10:00,933
Here you go again.

193
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,400
I've been loyal to you
since the year 2000.

194
00:10:03,533 --> 00:10:05,133
Since we got married.

195
00:10:05,267 --> 00:10:09,100
Oh really? So, that means you're
not loyal before the year 2000?

196
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:10,400
My gosh, Abel!

197
00:10:10,533 --> 00:10:12,667
Darling, that was 25 years ago!

198
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:15,067
- What are you so mad about!
- You'd better make sure!

199
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,333
Whoever that woman was,

200
00:10:16,467 --> 00:10:17,467
that would be your last one!

201
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:22,200
If not, you won't live to see
the light of day!

202
00:10:28,367 --> 00:10:31,600
So, we'll just run
a few more tests

203
00:10:31,733 --> 00:10:34,667
and if everything turns out
well, we can discharge her.

204
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:37,200
So, if you need anything else,
just text me.

205
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:38,267
I'll be doing my rounds.

206
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,733
- Thank you, Doctor.
- Thank you, Doctor.

207
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:43,067
Stop worrying, Manuel.

208
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,633
We'll be bringing
Jessica home soon.

209
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:48,233
I'm thinking about Hazel.

210
00:10:48,367 --> 00:10:50,667
She might cause trouble
for Jessica again.

211
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:55,667
Don't worry.

212
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:59,033
Manuel won't push through
with the lawsuit.

213
00:10:59,167 --> 00:11:01,167
He knows it was an accident.

214
00:11:02,433 --> 00:11:03,867
He knows I'm innocent.

215
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:08,233
And Jessica's okay now.

216
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:10,033
Jessica is awake, yes.

217
00:11:11,067 --> 00:11:12,967
But that doesn't necessarily
mean she's in good health.

218
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,267
You know that.

219
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,500
Of course.

220
00:11:16,933 --> 00:11:17,967
But I'm a nurse.

221
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:21,000
I checked her records.

222
00:11:23,067 --> 00:11:24,400
Everything's normal.

223
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:26,700
She's fine.

224
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,000
My daughter is fine.

225
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:31,367
I know.

226
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:32,667
I know because...

227
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,800
I'm her mom.

228
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,967
I can feel...

229
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,600
that she's okay.

230
00:11:42,767 --> 00:11:44,467
She's a fighter like me.

231
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:45,967
She's strong.

232
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,600
I just need...

233
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:53,067
to focus on her,
I need to take care of her.

234
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:55,800
<i> You're my mom too!</i>

235
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:57,200
<i> You're a nurse,</i>

236
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,167
<i>And you take care of strangers.</i>

237
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:01,833
<i>But you couldn't even
take care of me.</i>

238
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,833
I want to make it up to her.

239
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:09,367
Felma, I know Hazel.

240
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,300
She'll always find a way
to get in.

241
00:12:12,433 --> 00:12:13,700
Look at what she did earlier.

242
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,867
She pretended to be a doctor
so she could sneak in.

243
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:20,367
We'll stop her from coming here.

244
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:26,800
We will protect Jessica.

245
00:12:29,967 --> 00:12:35,000
I used to think that if I gave
her everything she needed,

246
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:36,733
that would be enough.

247
00:12:36,867 --> 00:12:38,233
That it would be okay.

248
00:12:38,367 --> 00:12:40,567
But it's not, she's right.

249
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,100
I didn't do enough!

250
00:12:43,867 --> 00:12:45,067
I need to make amends,

251
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,300
I need to make it up to her.

252
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:50,100
I want to rebuild
our family here.

253
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:54,500
Isn't that why I applied
for a job in the first place?

254
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:56,133
I understand, Hazel.

255
00:12:56,267 --> 00:12:58,167
But don't rush things just yet.

256
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,767
Focus on your work first.

257
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:03,333
Don't force yourself
on Jessica for now.

258
00:13:03,467 --> 00:13:04,467
No.

259
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,100
Please wait for the right time.

260
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:07,400
When is the right time?

261
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:13,200
My daughter is afraid of me.

262
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:17,633
I need to find a way
to talk to her.

263
00:13:19,933 --> 00:13:24,733
To make her understand
that that Felma is the reason

264
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:27,400
why our family fell apart.

265
00:13:28,533 --> 00:13:31,633
I don't want her to be scared
of me all her life.

266
00:13:32,967 --> 00:13:36,033
I can't bear it,
Jessica is my flesh and blood.

267
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:38,433
I will do everything.

268
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:41,300
Even if I have to tear down all
the walls of that hospital,

269
00:13:43,033 --> 00:13:45,767
just to talk to her,
just to see my child.

270
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,867
Miss, excuse me.

271
00:14:01,533 --> 00:14:03,667
Where's my sister?
The patient in this room?

272
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,400
Her name is Jessica Cruz.

273
00:14:05,633 --> 00:14:07,333
They transferred her
to a private room.

274
00:14:07,467 --> 00:14:08,933
She's awake now.

275
00:14:10,167 --> 00:14:13,767
Oh, thank God, she's okay now.

276
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:16,000
Did they just transfer her?

277
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:18,000
She was transferred a while ago,
after lunch.

278
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,400
Mom didn't even text or call me.

279
00:14:38,067 --> 00:14:40,767
- What the heck, Joel?
- Sorry, sorry, sorry.

280
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:42,700
I told you I'm coming over.

281
00:14:42,833 --> 00:14:44,267
You didn't even put on a shirt.

282
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,733
Put a shirt on.

283
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:47,900
So what's the good news?
How come you brought a cake?

284
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:54,500
Did you get the job
as a virtual assistant?

285
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:55,533
Congrats!

286
00:14:55,667 --> 00:14:56,933
Thank you.

287
00:14:57,067 --> 00:14:59,333
My brother's supposed
to celebrate with me right now.

288
00:14:59,467 --> 00:15:02,667
But he seems busy,
he's not answering my calls.

289
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:03,933
So I came here
to celebrate with you.

290
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:10,367
You're smiling way too wide!

291
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,400
Don't think that you're special.

292
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:15,933
I'm just used to celebrating
with my family

293
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:18,733
whenever I have achievements.

294
00:15:18,867 --> 00:15:20,267
And since they're not here...

295
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:24,633
I have another piece
of good news.

296
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:29,467
My work schedule is flexible.

297
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,900
I was assigned to calendar
and management.

298
00:15:32,033 --> 00:15:35,533
So I have a lot of time
in my hands.

299
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:38,667
So I'm looking for sideline jobs

300
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:41,000
and business opportunities.

301
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:45,967
So I can buy my own place,
a car,

302
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,967
and I can travel.

303
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:50,167
Take it easy.

304
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:51,567
Don't rush too much,

305
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:52,600
you'll get there in time.

306
00:15:53,633 --> 00:15:55,233
No, Joel.

307
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:57,733
I want it right away.

308
00:15:57,867 --> 00:15:59,800
So I can prove to my mom

309
00:15:59,933 --> 00:16:04,000
that I can make it
even without her support.

310
00:16:04,133 --> 00:16:06,333
That I'll be successful.

311
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:07,600
Just like you.

312
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:10,867
Wow, so you see me
as an inspiration?

313
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,767
Yes, why not?

314
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:17,400
Well, aside from the condo units
you're renting out,

315
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:19,700
you've got a lot of other
sources of income.

316
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,967
I want to be like that, too.

317
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,167
Actually, this high school
friend of mine.

318
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:26,900
- Okay.
- She said she has

319
00:16:27,033 --> 00:16:28,967
a business opportunity for me.

320
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:30,333
She just called me earlier.

321
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:33,567
What kind of business?

322
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:36,500
She'll tell me about it later.

323
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:40,400
As long as it's legit,
go for it.

324
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:47,600
Just let them know, okay?

325
00:16:47,733 --> 00:16:49,600
We'll take care of everything.

326
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:52,100
Yes, okay, thank you.

327
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,633
Jessica!

328
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:01,467
Coleen.

329
00:17:02,633 --> 00:17:04,333
Thank God, you're awake now.

330
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:06,633
I didn't get any sleep worrying

331
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:09,200
that you might not wake up.

332
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,867
Is that possible?

333
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:14,333
I can't leave you behind,
especially you, Coleen.

334
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:18,333
We still have so much
to go through together.

335
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:22,100
And we just started
to become a family.

336
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:26,800
Mom...

337
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:31,033
you didn't call me
that she has transferred rooms.

338
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:33,600
I didn't know that Jessica
was awake.

339
00:17:33,733 --> 00:17:35,433
I've been worrying about her
while at school.

340
00:17:35,567 --> 00:17:38,500
And then I went straight
to the ICU.

341
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:41,333
Sweetie...

342
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:46,300
you know what,
I was gonna call you.

343
00:17:46,433 --> 00:17:48,933
But a lot has happened earlier.

344
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:51,800
You know what,
Hazel was here earlier.

345
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:56,933
I thought you forgot about me.

346
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:59,533
Do you think
I'll forget about you?

347
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:01,600
Come on, I'm sorry, Sweetie.

348
00:18:01,733 --> 00:18:04,567
I'm sorry.

349
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:07,367
- Come on, smile.
- I want longanisa, Mom.

350
00:18:11,367 --> 00:18:13,600
Look at dad, he's smiling.

351
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:23,233
Yes, Sis. I got it!

352
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:24,567
<i> Great.</i>

353
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:28,800
Well...

354
00:18:28,933 --> 00:18:30,200
Look.

355
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:32,600
Wait, are you okay now?

356
00:18:32,733 --> 00:18:35,600
Yes, I'm okay now.

357
00:18:35,733 --> 00:18:36,800
You know me!

358
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:38,633
I knew it!

359
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:41,467
No one can bring down
a witch like you.

360
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:45,500
All right, I'll see you on your
first day.

361
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:47,267
See you!

362
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:53,500
I'll get the door, wait.

363
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,833
- Hey, what are you doing here?
- Oh, classmate.

364
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:00,767
I thought you didn't need
my help anymore?

365
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:02,267
What happened?

366
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:04,033
That's what I thought too.

367
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:05,567
But I have no choice.

368
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:09,500
So how can I help you, Madam?

369
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:13,467
I got banned at San Rafael
Doctor's Hospital.

370
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,800
You made a scene again,
didn't you?

371
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:18,700
Like what you did at Felma's
house before.

372
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:20,900
Help me get inside.

373
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:24,533
Sis, you might get caught.

374
00:19:24,667 --> 00:19:26,000
You might lose your job
because of it.

375
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:28,367
Relax, It's a different
hospital.

376
00:19:28,533 --> 00:19:30,467
And did you think
I'll let myself get caught?

377
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,633
So, are you going
to help me, Maximo?

378
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:35,633
Of course, where do you want
to enter?

379
00:19:35,767 --> 00:19:37,133
The back? The side?

380
00:19:37,267 --> 00:19:38,167
Sa basement parking?

381
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:40,933
The annex? Or the main entrance?

382
00:19:41,067 --> 00:19:42,333
What a show off.

383
00:19:42,467 --> 00:19:44,667
The question is,
can you sneak me in?

384
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:46,800
Of course, classmate.

385
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:49,433
I used to be a cop, remember?

386
00:19:51,967 --> 00:19:53,167
Good.

387
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:58,600
Yes, Mayette,

388
00:19:58,733 --> 00:20:01,533
I invested in Elvie's
lending business.

389
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:05,600
Joel said that if I ever get
a business opportunity,

390
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:07,600
I should go for it as long
as it's legit.

391
00:20:07,733 --> 00:20:09,100
<i> Wait. Elvie...</i>

392
00:20:09,233 --> 00:20:10,467
<i> Elvie Uy?</i>

393
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:14,100
<i> Our high school salutatorian?</i>

394
00:20:14,233 --> 00:20:15,567
<i> So is it really legit?</i>

395
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:19,633
Yes, and she has
a trustworthy reputation.

396
00:20:19,767 --> 00:20:21,667
And look at her post
on Friendsbook,

397
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:22,700
it's impressive, right?

398
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:23,867
<i> Of course.</i>

399
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,833
She already has two houses,
doesn't she?

400
00:20:25,967 --> 00:20:29,233
She has condo units, three cars,

401
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:31,100
and a sports car.

402
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:33,667
Right? She told me
she built everything

403
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,067
just from her lending business.

404
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:37,200
Impressive, isn't it?

405
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:38,733
So, you should invest too.

406
00:20:38,867 --> 00:20:40,300
You and Joel can do it together.

407
00:20:40,433 --> 00:20:42,600
Go! I'll do that,
I'll invest too.

408
00:20:42,733 --> 00:20:43,900
Hey, wait a minute...

409
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:48,433
you've brought up Joel's name
several times now.

410
00:20:48,567 --> 00:20:49,967
Is he your boyfriend?

411
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,100
No, he's not!

412
00:20:51,233 --> 00:20:52,433
We're just friends.

413
00:20:54,300 --> 00:20:56,900
Whatever, Andrea!

414
00:20:57,033 --> 00:20:58,000
Be honest with me!

415
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:02,767
What?

416
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:07,033
She was drunk, and you didn't
take advantage?

417
00:21:07,167 --> 00:21:09,100
What happened to you?

418
00:21:09,267 --> 00:21:10,833
I wanted to touch her.

419
00:21:10,967 --> 00:21:12,133
I don't know what happened.

420
00:21:12,267 --> 00:21:13,167
I couldn't do it.

421
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:15,133
I feel ashamed, I backed out.

422
00:21:15,267 --> 00:21:16,667
She seems so pure.

423
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,400
Don't tell me you're smitten.

424
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:27,733
Joel's a nice guy,
that's why we get along.

425
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:29,067
He's...

426
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:33,867
He's my first guy
friend since...

427
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:37,800
<i>Since elementary school,
when Uncle Manuel left.</i>

428
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:40,233
And you cursed all the men
out there.

429
00:21:40,367 --> 00:21:42,733
So what's going on?
Did Joel finally lift the curse?

430
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:46,733
No, we just have
a platonic relationship.

431
00:21:46,867 --> 00:21:49,167
So knock it off.

432
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:52,367
And...

433
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:54,533
I really don't have any plans
of getting a boyfriend.

434
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:58,600
Bro, Andrea is total
girlfriend material.

435
00:21:58,733 --> 00:22:02,933
She's fierce, brave,
but also vulnerable.

436
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:04,933
She's the kind of woman
you want to help.

437
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,233
You would want her to heal
her wounds.

438
00:22:09,167 --> 00:22:10,633
What?

439
00:22:10,767 --> 00:22:12,067
Unbelievable.

440
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,433
Since when did you become
serious?

441
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:17,200
Just now.

442
00:22:18,133 --> 00:22:20,967
You know, I grew up around
my mom's friends.

443
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:22,067
Easy to get.

444
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:24,167
They were just my past time,

445
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:26,433
a source of income...

446
00:22:26,567 --> 00:22:27,700
someone to sweet-talk.

447
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:29,700
You know what I mean?

448
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:32,333
Sleep with them,
then move on to the next.

449
00:22:32,467 --> 00:22:35,133
But Andrea's different.

450
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:42,200
Whoever evil spirit you are
who possessed my friend,

451
00:22:42,333 --> 00:22:43,567
please let him go.

452
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,000
What the heck, Bro.

453
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:48,933
People can change, you know?

454
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:50,933
Some do, yes. But you?

455
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:56,133
Wait a minute, don't tell me
you're going to pursue her.

456
00:22:57,600 --> 00:23:00,267
I don't think Joel
will pursue me.

457
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,633
I don't think I'm his type.

458
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:05,333
He doesn't seem like a serious
type either,

459
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:08,000
He doesn't take women seriously.

460
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:09,567
He seems like a player.

461
00:23:10,967 --> 00:23:13,167
He just likes to flirt.

462
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:16,900
So, did he flirt with you?

463
00:23:17,933 --> 00:23:20,167
I think he was flirting with me
at first.

464
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:25,800
But then, I think he realized
it wouldn't work with me.

465
00:23:25,967 --> 00:23:29,233
So just drop it, okay?

466
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:30,833
Because we're just friends.

467
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:31,867
That's all there is to it.

468
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,700
Okay, fine!

469
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:36,033
Whatever you say.

470
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:39,200
But you know what? What a waste.

471
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:41,133
I really thought my bestie
was finally going to get

472
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:43,667
a taste of her first kiss.

473
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:44,800
Yuck!

474
00:23:44,933 --> 00:23:45,933
What the heck!

475
00:23:47,433 --> 00:23:48,800
You're insane.

476
00:23:48,933 --> 00:23:50,567
<i>So are you going to pursue her?</i>

477
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:51,667
Yes.

478
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:55,267
I will pursue her...

479
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,800
so I can love her,

480
00:23:58,367 --> 00:24:00,433
take care of her,

481
00:24:00,567 --> 00:24:01,867
and marry her.

482
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:04,267
Unbelievable!

483
00:24:06,033 --> 00:24:07,500
It's over then.

484
00:24:07,633 --> 00:24:09,033
We have a winner!

485
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:13,667
I really have to carry this?

486
00:24:15,167 --> 00:24:16,167
What are you doing?

487
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:17,033
Just chill.

488
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:19,333
You want to go inside, right?

489
00:24:27,733 --> 00:24:29,667
Take your mask off, please.

490
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:34,833
Sir...

491
00:24:34,967 --> 00:24:36,033
my wife is pregnant.

492
00:24:36,167 --> 00:24:37,967
She might inhale germs
and bacteria.

493
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:39,633
I don't want her to get sick.

494
00:24:39,867 --> 00:24:42,033
So how's your duty going?

495
00:24:42,167 --> 00:24:44,033
Here you go, to keep you
guys awake.

496
00:24:44,167 --> 00:24:45,233
Oh, wow!

497
00:24:45,367 --> 00:24:46,433
You went out of your way
to bring this.

498
00:24:46,567 --> 00:24:47,667
- Thank you, thanks.
- Oh, no, especially you.

499
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:50,200
That's the new Glock model!

500
00:24:50,333 --> 00:24:52,300
Nice! The recoil looks nice.

501
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:55,233
In my opinion,

502
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:57,567
I still like the standard issue
we had before.

503
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:00,600
The quality is good...

504
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:02,767
and it's reliable!

505
00:25:02,933 --> 00:25:03,833
Are you a police officer?

506
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:05,633
Not just any officer,

507
00:25:05,767 --> 00:25:06,900
I'm one of the best.

508
00:25:07,033 --> 00:25:10,033
Remember the South West
Trust Bank robbery?

509
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:11,433
Back in 2023?

510
00:25:12,933 --> 00:25:15,500
I was the one who took down
those two robbers!

511
00:25:15,633 --> 00:25:17,433
<i> Hon, Hon.</i>

512
00:25:17,567 --> 00:25:18,600
Sorry, Honey.

513
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:19,800
Excuse me, Boss.
where's the restroom?

514
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:21,067
I'm sorry but...

515
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,733
- my wife needs to use it.
- Go straight, then right.

516
00:25:22,867 --> 00:25:23,933
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

517
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:25,633
What took you so long?

518
00:25:26,067 --> 00:25:28,100
Jessica's room
is on the fourth floor,

519
00:25:28,233 --> 00:25:29,500
Room 411.

520
00:25:29,633 --> 00:25:31,300
I'll go with you
till the fire exit.

521
00:25:31,433 --> 00:25:33,567
Take the stairs, they don't have
cameras that way.

522
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:35,267
If you want,
I can go with you...

523
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:37,067
No, no. I got this.

524
00:25:37,233 --> 00:25:38,133
- Okay.
- Are you sure?

525
00:25:38,267 --> 00:25:39,500
Felma might see you.

526
00:25:39,633 --> 00:25:41,233
Then you'll get in a fight
and get hurt again.

527
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:42,467
No, I know what to do.

